CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1949, pg. 11, reads: "Annual Tea - The Senior Choir of Trinity Baptist Church held its annual tea in home of Mr. and Mrs. V. N. Reed, 3047 Penn Avenue. Among those seated, are: The Rev. and Mrs. W. W. Wingfield and Mr. and Mrs. V. N. Reed.  Standing are the members of the choir and friends. The Rev. W. W. Wingfield is pastor. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of choir and members of Trinity Baptist Church, including Rev. W. W. Wingfield, Mrs. Wingfield, V. N. Reed, and Mrs. Reed, posed in front of Reed's home, 3047 (and 3049) Penn Avenue, Strip District
